  "prompt": "How can I retrieve saved messages in Snapchat that got deleted when person unfriended me?",
  "response": "When someone unfriends you on Snapchat, any saved messages you shared with that person typically remain visible to both parties unless they are manually deleted. However, if messages seem to have disappeared after the unfriending, it can be challenging to retrieve them. Here are a few options you might consider:\n\n1. **Check Snapchat Memories**: If you have saved any messages or chats to your Snapchat Memories, you can check there to see if they are still accessible.\n\n2. **Check Archived Chats**: Sometimes, archived chats may still be visible even if the contact is no longer on your friends list. Scroll through your chat history to see if the conversation is still listed.\n\n3. **Contact Snapchat Support**: Though it's a long shot, you can try reaching out to Snapchat's support team. They might not be able to recover the messages, but it doesn\u2019t hurt to ask.\n\n4. **Check for Screenshots or Backups**: If you or the other person took screenshots of the chat, or if you have any backups of your phone that might include Snapchat data, you might find the messages there.\n\n5. **Re-add the Person**: If possible, try re-adding the person to see if the chat history becomes accessible again.\n\nRemember, Snapchat is designed to prioritize user privacy by not storing message content long-term, so retrieving deleted messages can be difficult. It's always good practice to manually save important information elsewhere if you think you might need it for future reference.",
